-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_billing_events.sql
-- Deduplicate billing_events to one row per subscription/month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_id,
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- models/mart/fct_subscription_metrics.sql
-- Monthly subscription metrics grouped by tier and industry
WITH joined_data AS (
    SELECT
        be.event_month,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry,
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        be.amount
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }} be
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
        ON s.subscription_id = be.subscription_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = s.plan_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
        ON u.user_id = s.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
        ON c.company_id = u.company_id
)
SELECT
    event_month AS month,
    tier,
    industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
FROM joined_data
GROUP BY
    event_month,
    tier,
    industry
ORDER BY
    event_month DESC,
    tier,
    industry
